\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-142\li142\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Write a program that performs basic arithmetic operations (addition, subtraction, \par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 multiplication, and division).\par
o Prompt the user to enter two numbers and choose an operation (+, -, *, /).\par
o Perform the chosen operation and display the result.\par
o Handle division by zero errors with a suitable message.\par
def simple_calculator():\par
    try:\par
        num1 = float(input("Enter the first number: "))\par
        num2 = float(input("Enter the second number: "))\par
        operation = input("Enter the operation (+, -, *, /): ").strip()\par
        if operation == '+':\par
            result = num1 + num2\par
        elif operation == '-':\par
            result = num1 - num2\par
        elif operation == '*':\par
            result = num1 * num2\par
        elif operation == '/':\par
            if num2 == 0:\par
                print("Error: Division by zero.")\par
                return\par
            result = num1 / num2\par
        else:\par
            print("Invalid operation.")\par
            return\par
        print(f"The result is: \{result\}")\par
    except ValueError:\par
        print("Invalid input.")\par
simple_calculator()\par
