\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-142\li142\sa200\sl276\slmult1  Write a program that randomly selects a number between 1 and 10.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 o Prompt the user to guess the number.\par
o Provide feedback if the guess is too high or too low.\par
o Allow the user to guess again until they \f1\u976?ind the correct number.\par
o Print a congratulatory message when the correct number is guessed.\par
\lang1032 import random\par
def number_guessing_game():\par
    number_to_guess = random.randint(1, 10)\par
    print("Welcome to the Number Guessing Game!")\par
    while True:\par
        try:\par
            guess = int(input("Guess the number between 1 and 10: "))\par
            if guess < 1 or guess > 10:\par
                print("Please enter a number between 1 and 10.")\par
                continue\par
            if guess < number_to_guess:\par
                print("Too low. Try again.")\par
            elif guess > number_to_guess:\par
                print("Too high. Try again.")\par
            else:\par
                print("Congratulations! You guessed the correct number.")\par
                break\par
        except ValueError:\par
            print("Invalid input. Please enter a number.")\par
number_guessing_game()\par
